<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-28T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-28T18:00:00-05:00" n="48" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee
                                (Arms)/163: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-28T18:00:00-05:00">March
                                        28, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>490. Your 1027, March 27, 11 a.m. We feel strongly that the
                                Committees should write a single text with reservations rather than
                                writing a text in two columns.</p>
                            <p>In view of the general political situation we incline to favor the
                                idea of continuing to work in private. We feel that if reservations
                                of importance are entered by only one or two States, the pressure of
                                public opinion to induce them to withdraw those reservations would
                                be just as effective as public opinion mobilized at this time to
                                prevent their insertion and the attendant dangers of an acrimonious
                                public debate would be avoided.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>